Executive Profile
Melinda R. Rich  Vice chairman, Executive Vice President of Innovation and President of Rich Entertainment Group, Rich Products CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mrs. Melinda R. Rich, also known as Mindy, has been President of Rich Entertainment Group since 1994 and has been its Executive Vice President of Innovation since 1997. Mrs. Rich is responsible for overseeing the Rich organization's baseball, entertainment and travel interests including: The Buffalo Bisons of the International League, Triple-A affiliate of the Cleveland Indians; Double-A Wichita Wranglers of the Texas League; and the Single-A Jamestown Jammers of the ... New York Penn League. B.R. Guest, Ltd. including Fanfare Concessions; The Glen Iris Inn; Letchworth State Park; Palm Beach National Golf & Country Club; Pettibones Grille; Prestige Pastries; Rich Renaissance Niagara Conference Center; Renaissance Catering; and Rich's Bakery Outlet Store. She has been Vice Chairman of Rich Products Corporation since August 22, 2006. Mrs. Rich joined the Rich organization in 1985 from Westwood Pharmaceuticals. She founded Western New York United and Alcohol Abuse in 1986. She serves as Vice Chairman of Rich Products Ltd. Mrs. Rich has been a Director of Rich Products Corporation since 1998. She serves as a Director of M&T Bank, Inc. Mrs. Rich serves as a Director of the Erie Canal Harbor Development Corporation as well as Cleveland Clinics Wellness Institute Leadership Board. She serves as a director of several charitable foundations including the Rich Family Foundation, Dream Catcher Foundation, Inc. and The Don Hawley Foundation and TheCulinary Institute of America. She has been an Independent Director at M&T Bank Corporation since 2009. She served as a Director of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company since 1999. She served as a Director of M&T Bank, a subsidiary of M&T Bank Corporation. Mrs. Rich served as a Director of M&T Asset Management. She has received numerous awards and honors including induction into the Western New York Women's Hall of Fame in 2004; Honorary Doctorate of Humane Letters Degree from the Culinary Institute of America in 2001; Buffalo Baseball Hall of Fame Induction in 1999; Pathfinder's Award in 1997; Erie County Sheriff's Foundation Community Service Award in 1996; induction as an Honorary Brother of the Alpha Kappa Psi Fraternity at Canisius College in 1993; Rita Webb Smith Citizen Drug Fighter of the Year Award from former New York Governor Mario Cuomo's Anti-Drug Abuse Council in 1992; and the American Jewish Committee's Institute of Human Relations' (Buffalo Chapter) Woman of the Year in 1992. Mrs. Rich holds Bachelor of Arts in Psychology from University of Colorado at Boulder. She received Honorary Doctorate of Laws from D'Youville College in 2007. She holds Honorary Doctorate in Humane Letters from The Culinary Institute Of America in 2001.Read Full Background




