Rich Entertainment Group










 





Rich Entertainment Group (REG) is a diverse holding company that operates sports teams, produces theatrical entertainment and offers unique hospitality and travel experiences by providing platforms where talent can flourish.
Aside from the Tony-nominated musical ON YOUR FEET currently on Broadway, REG has several upcoming theatrical projects in development including Bull Durham and Escape to Margaritaville. Past productions include Tuck Everlasting, Clybourne Park, Jesus Christ Superstar, Leap of Faith, Chaplin the Musical and Big Fish.


 


 



 





Melinda R.  Rich - President, Rich Entertainment Group
              Melinda  (“Mindy”) is Vice Chairman of Rich Products Corporation and serves on the Board of Trustees of the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame  and Museum and the Culinary Institute of America. She also serves on the board of M&T Bank. She is involved in a vast  array of charitable causes, especially fundraising efforts that are geared  towards finding a cure for cystic fibrosis. Mindy has a diverse work background that includes  involvement in sports, advertising and public relations, event management, video production,  radio stations, and ticketing companies. Mindy has received numerous honors and  awards include two honorary doctorates and induction into the Western New York  Women’s Hall of Fame in 2004. She is also a past board member for Shea's Performing Arts Center in Buffalo, NY.


 
 



Robert E. Rich,  Jr. - Vice  President, Rich Entertainment Group
              Bob is Chairman of Rich Products Corporation and currently serves as Chairman of  Cleveland Clinic. Throughout  his prestigious career, he has been the recipient of dozens of honors and  awards, including five honorary doctorate degrees, professorships at the University  of Pennsylvania and the George Bush Presidential Library, and inclusion in  several halls of fame. He is also the author of several non-fiction books on a  variety of topics, and he supports and leads many charitable causes. 


 
 


 
